text:
Sutphin Boulevard,(foreground) at the S.W. corner of One Hundred Twentieth Ave. The one and one-half story bungalows face on One Hundred Twentieth Ave. The house in the foreground is just north of the Geo. Hegeman property. Eugene L. Armbruster questionably refers to this property as that of A. Dunham, 1860-1873; McMason, 1891; and the Mason Estate in 1896.

April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
